153
00:09:05,861 --> 00:09:09,904
Mr. President, through you to the members, this is a very straightforward request.

154
00:09:10,185 --> 00:09:23,996
It is to establish a revolving fund that will allow fees and costs associated with delinquent tax cases to be put into this fund and then

155
00:09:24,817 --> 00:09:28,139
would be able to pay the costs associated with those cases.

156
00:09:28,639 --> 00:09:30,560
It wouldn't be subject to appropriation.

157
00:09:30,720 --> 00:09:44,187
It would be pretty much a pass-through account where when we get a bill for our legal fees or our fees from the registry, they would already have been paid by the delinquent taxpayer.

158
00:09:44,207 --> 00:09:46,128
We take it out of that account and pay the fees.

159
00:09:47,982 --> 00:09:54,744
The Department of Revenue has made a general recommendation that all cities and towns accept this statute.

160
00:09:55,224 --> 00:10:03,526
It's a cleaner, more transparent way to see how funds are being expended to recoup tax title funds.

161
00:10:04,566 --> 00:10:04,866
Thank you.

162
00:10:05,326 --> 00:10:06,106
Council Member Kern.

163
00:10:06,787 --> 00:10:08,747
